				<h3><a href="http://grantland.com/hollywood-prospectus/david-o-russell-accidental-love-career-arc/" >The Two David O. Russells</a></h3>
				<div class="byline"><em>by</em> <a class="fn" href="http://grantland.com/contributors/steven-hyden/">Steven Hyden</a></div>				<blockquote>
					<p><a href="http://grantland.com/hollywood-prospectus/david-o-russell-accidental-love-career-arc/">What story did Russell see in ‘The Fighter’? Could it be an allegory about who he was and who he wanted to become? In the film, Mark Wahlberg’s aspiring boxing champion has to contend with a brother, played by Christian Bale, whom he loves but whose impulsivity and bad reputation threaten to drag Wahlberg down. Bale used to be the favorite son of his hometown, but he has derailed his life and eventually winds up in prison, just as Russell was stuck in professional purgatory.</a></p>
